<h4>
    Rules for an object moving in a circle
</h4>

<ol class = 'principleList'>
    <li>
        Whenever an object is moving in a circle, its <emph>velocity</emph> is <emph>tangent</emph> to the circle.
    </li>
    <li>
        Whenever an object is moving in a circle, there is a <emph>force</emph> pulling it <emph>towards the center</emph>
        of the circle.
        This force is called the <strong>centripetal force</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
        If the centripetal force is released, the object will fly in a straight line <emph>tangent</emph> to the circle,
        in the direction of its velocity the moment it was released.
        It <strong>never</strong> continues to turn or bend, but always moves in a straight line.
    </li>
</ol>

